$ vim script - regular expressions: Non greedy matches

A `*` matches with greed (that is: as much as possible).

To match as little as necessary, use `\{-}` (or with magic: `{-}`)

gh|about-vim|/regular_expressions/non_greedy.vim||

sa:

  → development/vim/script/regular_expressions

  → development/vim/script/index

